This is exactly why testing regularly with @insidetracker is necessary for me🙏🏼 #ad It was LOVELY to find out that my ferritin is at 20 and still trending downwards🙃. Low ferritin levels reduce the capacity to deliver oxygen to the muscles, which will negatively impact performance, and can cause shortness of breath and fatigue. It is SUPER important to keep track of your ferritin levels, especially female endurance athletes since we lose more blood through menstruation each month. My normal range is 35-45 so I started taking iron supplements after my workouts and adding in more beans🫘, red meat🥩, & vegetables🥦🌱 to my diet. Hoping to see some improvement the next time I test! Use code EMMA20 for 20% OFF @insidetracker's website as always!

First wake up, oatmeal, coffee. Then send it on a 5 mile recovery run right along the beach🏃🏼‍♀️ #ad & straight to @24HourFitness for a quick strength/mobility session & now I am absolutely craving a little sweet treat😋. Refueling is such an important part of my fitness routine, whether I’m running outside or just finished a session at @24HourFitness, and today I got into the holiday spirit by making some PEPPERMINT PROTEIN BROWNIES🍫🌱

ingredients:

-1 can chickpeas
-1/2 cup almond butter
-1/3 cup maple syrup
-1/8 tsp peppermint extract
-1/2 tsp vanilla extract
-2 tbsp cocoa powder
-1/2 tsp baking soda
-1/2 tsp baking powder
-1/4 tsp sea salt
-1/4 cup chocolate chips🍫
-3 tbsp chopped peppermints

directions:

in a food processor combine all wet ingredients until chickpeas are fully puréed. scrape the sides. add in cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda & sea salt and combine. pulse in chocolate chips. press into 8x8 pan and bake at 350 for 25 minutes. sprinkle peppermints on top right after taking pan out of the oven. cut into 9 squares & store in fridge. best served cold. ENJOY!

I know I joke a lot on here but honestly 2022 was the most challenging & transformative year of my life. It genuinely brought me the highest highs & lowest lows. However, 2022 was the year I got my spark back. I don’t know how to explain it but I feel like I’ve been missing a piece of my personality for 10 years and somewhere along the way this year I found it again. To the new friends & community I’ve made in SD, I am grateful. To my old friends, thanks for continuing to fill my life with so much joy. I’ve also found my love for running again & have a renewed sense of its purpose in my life. I don’t know what 2023 will have in store but all I know is I am going to embrace whatever is thrown at me! welcome to my @nikerunning shoe rotation👟🏃🏼‍♀️:

-My OG favorite Pegasus 40: these are my trusty steeds. They are a neutral shoe that I can wear on any terrain for basically any workout!
-My go-to Invincible Run 3’s: when I need extra cushion for my training runs, this is my staple pair of shoes. These I wear solely for training & recovery running, no workouts. They help me bounce back quick and recover for the next hard session. 
-The new Infinity Run 4’s: made with ReactX foam which makes for a bouncy, smooth recovery run with a high level of support. Highly recommend as the newest addition to your trainer rotation! I wear them on my easy run days on the road.
